{"change_summary":"Consolidated milestone completion-detail formatting into a shared `model.rs` helper used by both service-side journal writes and filesystem repair merges, documented the parser’s `\", \"` delimiter assumption for identifier fields, tightened `FsTaskRunLineageStore::update_task_run` so a requested `run_id` only falls back to a legacy runless open row when it is the sole open attempt, and upgraded task-run collapse/query handling to merge replayed terminal rows for the same attempt instead of reporting them as extra retries. Added regression coverage for duplicate-terminal bead queries, mixed legacy/named open-attempt ambiguity, and terminal replay deduplication at the model layer.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone mutations still span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash between file writes can still leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same operation is replayed or state is reconciled from lineage."],"steps":[{"description":"Inspected the current milestone lineage, journal, and query code paths to map each pending amendment to the concrete `model.rs`, `service.rs`, and `fs.rs` change surface.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Moved completion journal-detail rendering to a shared milestone-model helper, switched both service writes and filesystem repair rendering to that helper, and documented the parser assumption that identifier fields never contain the `\", \"` delimiter.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Fixed `update_task_run` to reject ambiguous mixed legacy/named open attempts when a requested `run_id` has no exact match, instead of finalizing an arbitrary runless row.","order":2,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Extended attempt collapsing so legacy start/completion pairs and duplicate terminal replays for the same attempt collapse into one canonical entry, then added regression tests covering duplicate-terminal bead queries and the mixed-open-attempt ambiguity case.","order":3,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Ran formatting, milestone-record unit tests, and clippy validation after the changes.","order":4,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 83 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully."]}